      "description": "The [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} conjures a whirlwind at a point it can see within 120 feet. The whirlwind fills a [[lookup @target.template.size activity=TYNKL0QDItFpbR2G]]-foot-radius, [[lookup @target.template.height activity=TYNKL0QDItFpbR2G]]-foot-high [[lookup @target.template.type capitalize activity=TYNKL0QDItFpbR2G]] centered on that point. The whirlwind lasts until the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster}'s Concentration on it ends. The [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} can move the whirlwind up to 20 feet at the start of each of its turns.\n\nWhenever the whirlwind enters a creature's space or a creature enters the whirlwind, that creature is subjected to the following effect.\n\nStrength Saving Throw: DC [[lookup @save.dc.value activity=TYNKL0QDItFpbR2G]] (a creature makes this save only once per turn, and the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} is unaffected).\n\nFailure: While in the whirlwind, the target has the &amp;Reference[Restrained apply=false] condition and moves with the whirlwind. At the start of each of its turns, the Restrained target takes [[/damage average]] damage. At the end of each of its turns, the target repeats the save, ending the effect on itself on a success.",
      "kind": "action",
      "legendary_cost": null,
